# Testing Card

## Summary
The `Testing` card is a simple card specification that can be used within a consuming card or field.

## Import
```javascript
import { Testing } from '../testing';
```

## Usage as a Field
To use the `Testing` card as a field within a consuming card or field, you can add it as a `containsOne` or `containsMany` field:

```javascript
import { CardDef } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { Testing } from '../testing';

export class MyCard extends CardDef {
  static displayName = 'My Card';

  containsOne = {
    testing: Testing
  };
}
```

## Template Usage
To display the `Testing` card within a template, you can use the following syntax:

```hbs
<@fields.testing />
```

This will render the `Testing` card within the consuming card or field.
